-1 'IMM ENCHANT'~
Immortals will enchant your weapon or armor up to a maximum of +10.
This means +10 total, not 10 enchants on top of its current bonus.
The costs are as follows:

+1  = 1 quest token
+2  = 2 quest tokens
+3  = 3 quest tokens
+4  = 4 quest tokens
+5  = 5 quest tokens
+6  = 6 quest tokens
+7  = 7 quest tokens
+8  = 8 quest tokens
+9  = 9 quest tokens
+10 = 10 quest tokens

This means if you have an unenchanted sword and want it enchanted to +3,
it will cost you 1 token to get to +1, 2 tokens to get you to +2, and then
3 tokens to get to +3 for a total of 6 tokens.  If you have a sword which
is already +7 and you want it to get to +10, then it will cost 8+9+10= 27
quest tokens.

If the enchant increases the item by +2 instead of +1 you do not have to
pay extra--it's just your own good luck.
~

